{
  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25000 from their employer. As an accountant, they held a position of fiduciary responsibility which they abused. However, there are significant mitigating factors to consider. The defendant has no prior criminal history and has already engaged in partial restitution, demonstrating remorse and a willingness to make amends. Given the non-violent nature of the offense and the defendant's previously clean record, a substantial prison term is not appropriate. A brief period of incarceration is sufficient to serve as punitive action and deterrence, followed by supervised release to ensure the remainder of the restitution is paid.",
  "verdict": 6
}
